title: Westbound lanes of MD 450 in Maryland reopen
text:
Updated at 10:09 a.m.

All lanes on MD 450′s westbound side near Glenn Dale Boulevard in Prince George’s County have reopened after an earlier crash.

FINAL: Crash with Injuries. MD-450 WB past MD-193 (Glenn Dale Blvd). Prince George's County, MD. Incident cleared, all lanes open. — MATOC Alerts (@MATOC) September 17, 2019

Original post at 7:40 a.m.

Drivers should expect delays Tuesday morning after a crash blocked all westbound lanes of MD 450 near Glenn Dale Boulevard in Prince George’s County.
description: A crash caused delays along MD 450 westbound in Prince George's County.
